are we looking for

05:39.298 --> 05:41.133
-

05:41.216 --> 05:45.971
of the rhythm nation

05:50.392 --> 05:55.939
all I know is love

06:15.084 --> 06:17.961
Unhappy with the tea,
Stepmother?

06:18.045 --> 06:21.590
Imagine if you served such swill
to your future husband.

06:21.673 --> 06:23.842
How long would it take
for him to abandon you?

06:23.926 --> 06:26.804
To understand
just how worthless you are?

06:26.887 --> 06:29.056
Learn from this
and never do it again.

06:29.139 --> 06:31.433
I thought she was
rather hard on her.

06:31.517 --> 06:34.228
-I thought she could've
gone harder. -Quiet.

06:34.311 --> 06:36.647
Cinderella, now that
you're an orphan,

06:36.730 --> 06:38.857
it's important for you
to remember that

06:38.941 --> 06:41.276
it's only my love for
your father-- rest his soul--

06:41.360 --> 06:43.278
that stands between you
and a life on the street.

06:43.362 --> 06:46.615
Yes, of course. And that's why
I'm so thankful for...

06:46.698 --> 06:48.408
You could be so pretty...

06:48.492 --> 06:50.828
if you took even a second
to comb that hair of yours.

06:58.669 --> 07:01.171
Oh, you're in.
Good morning, Ella.

07:01.255 --> 07:03.173
Mr. Cecil.

07:03.257 --> 07:04.424
It's Mr. Cecil!

07:05.801 --> 07:07.886
I'm curious--
do you really need that cane?

07:07.970 --> 07:09.930
No, but chicks dig it.

07:10.013 --> 07:11.140
-Oh.
-THOMAS: Vivian.

07:11.223 --> 07:12.307
Thomas.

07:12.391 --> 07:13.559
And all the girls.

07:13.642 --> 07:14.935
Lucky Thomas.

07:15.018 --> 07:16.436
-There they go.

07:16.520 --> 07:17.729
Freshly picked from the farm.

07:17.813 --> 07:21.275
Parsnips, turnips, rutabagas.

07:21.358 --> 07:23.610
The fleshiest fruit
of the earth.

07:23.694 --> 07:25.404
Would you like to come in?

07:25.487 --> 07:28.240
Yes... N-No.

07:28.323 --> 07:31.326
No, no, not today. Yeah, I just
wanted to check in on you

07:31.410 --> 07:34.288
and make sure that your, uh,
blossoming daughters

07:34.371 --> 07:36.206
are, uh...

07:36.290 --> 07:38.125
um, managing.

07:38.208 --> 07:39.376
Makes my skin crawl.

07:39.459 --> 07:40.752
-Mine, too.
-I'm into it.

07:40.836 --> 07:41.920
All right, then.

07:42.004 --> 07:43.922
Now I've got this mental image

07:44.006 --> 07:46.884
to nourish me through the day,
I'll be going.

07:50.262 --> 07:51.388
CINDERELLA:
Ew.

07:55.184 --> 07:57.936
Fortune has smiled
upon this house.

07:58.937 --> 08:00.647
My daughters have a suitor.

08:00.731 --> 08:02.316
You mean this daughter
has a suitor.

08:02.399 --> 08:03.859
The others have
heartache and jealousy.

08:03.942 --> 08:05.360
Oh, ha-ha-ha.

08:05.444 --> 08:08.405
Yeah, no, I am not
a match for Thomas.

08:08.488 --> 08:11.241
Well, you must make yourself
a match for someone.

08:11.325 --> 08:13.243
Yes.

08:13.327 --> 08:15.370
I understand, Stepmother.

08:19.249 --> 08:20.459
Here comes our girl.

08:20.542 --> 08:21.835
Oh, boy, she's got heavy feet.

08:30.552 --> 08:32.471
JAMES:
Oh, I slept in that fabric.

08:32.554 --> 08:34.181
JOHN:
Shh!

08:47.110 --> 08:48.904
a world outside

08:56.870 --> 08:59.581
that understands

08:59.665 --> 09:01.541
the whispers

09:01.625 --> 09:03.919
you're walking in

09:09.174 --> 09:12.386
staring at me

09:12.469 --> 09:15.055
I know who I'm gonna be

09:16.848 --> 09:21.061
it's gonna wake up and see

09:21.144 --> 09:22.688
-Ooh.
-Ooh, nice.

09:29.194 --> 09:33.699
a shot in the dark

09:35.659 --> 09:39.913
to be wrong

09:46.336 --> 09:50.215
know my name

09:54.219 --> 09:56.054
is always racing

09:56.138 --> 09:58.432
round the room

10:00.350 --> 10:03.729
I don't wanna do

10:03.812 --> 10:06.732
staring at me

10:06.815 --> 10:09.776
I know who I'm gonna be

10:24.207 --> 10:27.544
a shot in the dark

10:27.627 --> 10:30.130
-

10:30.213 --> 10:32.966
-Oh!

10:40.724 --> 10:43.894
know my name

10:43.977 --> 10:49.066
now and then

10:50.567 --> 10:54.738
that I could be

10:58.825 --> 11:02.704
all along in her head

11:02.788 --> 11:08.085
is hard to see

11:18.220 --> 11:22.974
a shot in the dark

11:27.646 --> 11:29.439
-

11:29.523 --> 11:32.526
-

11:35.612 --> 11:38.615
-

11:41.451 --> 11:44.329
know my name, yeah

11:47.791 --> 11:51.420
know my name.

12:10.397 --> 12:12.732
God.

12:12.816 --> 12:14.734
That's disgusting.

12:15.694 --> 12:17.696
Well, thank you for coming in.

12:17.779 --> 12:20.282
Well, before your aide-de-camp
loses a hand...

12:20.365 --> 12:25.036
This is called a world map.

12:25.120 --> 12:28.498
Now, take a look
at this blob here and here.

12:28.582 --> 12:32.544
If we marry,
our blobs would join up,

12:32.627 --> 12:35.338
and we would control the world

12:35.422 --> 12:37.966
all the way
to this huge sea monster.

12:38.049 --> 12:39.009
Mm, the sea monster.

12:39.092 --> 12:40.260
You know, I really just

12:40.343 --> 12:41.845
don't have the time
in my schedule

12:41.928 --> 12:43.555
to be controlling
these far-off lands.

12:43.638 --> 12:45.765
I am just too busy.

12:45.849 --> 12:47.184
LAURA:
Doing what?

12:47.267 --> 12:50.187
You spent three whole days
drinking and foxhunting.

12:50.270 --> 12:51.480
That was a lot of hard work.

12:51.563 --> 12:53.064
Now, you try tracking a fox
when drunk.

12:53.148 --> 12:55.066
-It's impossible.
-No, it isn't!

12:56.109 --> 12:57.486
You didn't.

12:57.569 --> 12:59.237
-Do not hit me, sweet prince!
-

12:59.321 --> 13:01.031
No, no, no, no!

13:02.741 --> 13:04.534
I promise, milord,

13:04.618 --> 13:08.163
you can keep gallivanting here
with your merry bros,

13:08.246 --> 13:10.457
and I'll have other interests.

13:10.540 --> 13:12.709
We never have to be together,
except for royal events,

13:12.792 --> 13:14.961
war planning
and when we have to engage

13:15.045 --> 13:17.005
in the disgusting practice
of making a son.

13:17.088 --> 13:18.673
WILBUR:
Yeah?

13:18.757 --> 13:20.509
Your offer is intriguing,

13:20.592 --> 13:24.513
but I have no intention
on settling down anytime soon.

13:27.557 --> 13:28.767
I see.

13:31.770 --> 13:34.439
He's not working
with much upstairs,

13:34.523 --> 13:36.399
and I'd be surprised
if it was different elsewhere.

13:36.483 --> 13:38.360
-She knows what I'm
talking about. -

13:48.828 --> 13:51.414
yeah, I took over from Barry

13:51.498 --> 13:53.625
but he died of dysentery

13:53.708 --> 13:56.545
the announcements of the day

13:56.628 --> 13:59.256
you like the way they play

13:59.339 --> 14:01.299
for you ladies and gents

14:01.383 --> 14:03.969
is soon gonna commence

14:04.052 --> 14:06.429
better than the shire fair

14:06.513 --> 14:08.974
royal family will be there

14:09.057 --> 14:11.935
-

14:12.018 --> 14:13.937
and our Queen Beatrice

14:14.020 --> 14:16.523
you don't wanna miss

14:16.606 --> 14:19.067
Princess Gwen, no doubt

14:19.150 --> 14:21.820
and the old roll out

14:28.076 --> 14:29.411
Are they rosy yet?

14:29.494 --> 14:30.996
The pain is quite terrific.

14:31.079 --> 14:33.707
-Ladies, are we ready?

14:33.790 --> 14:35.500
What in God's name
are you doing?

14:35.584 --> 14:37.210
Bringing color to her cheeks.

14:37.294 --> 14:38.920
-Good idea.

14:39.004 --> 14:41.214
-Where's Cinderella?
-She's still in that basement.

14:41.298 --> 14:44.342
-Cinderella! -I'm starting
to think she doesn't like us.

14:44.426 --> 14:46.219
Cinderella!
Girls, can you help me?

14:46.303 --> 14:48.096
ALL:
Cinderella!

14:49.514 --> 14:51.766
STEPSISTERS
Cinderella!

14:54.269 --> 14:57.480
-VIVIAN: Cinderella!
-STEPSISTERS: Cinderella!

14:59.482 --> 15:00.442
You called?

15:00.525 --> 15:01.651
Yes, stepchild.

15:01.735 --> 15:02.861
Don't be dense.

15:02.944 --> 15:04.154
I'm sorry, I-I was just...

15:04.237 --> 15:05.322
About to make an excuse?

15:05.405 --> 15:06.740
I could truly care less.

15:06.823 --> 15:09.117
Grab your things.
Try not to make us late.

15:09.200 --> 15:11.161
The changing of the guard
waits for no one.

15:11.244 --> 15:12.370
Cinderella?

15:12.454 --> 15:13.872
Yeah?

15:13.955 --> 15:15.874
Do you think I look pretty?

15:15.957 --> 15:19.210
I think you look so pretty.

15:19.294 --> 15:21.212
But...

15:21.296 --> 15:23.923
honestly, who cares
what I think?

15:24.007 --> 15:25.925
Who cares what anyone thinks?

15:26.009 --> 15:28.637
What matters is how you feel
when you look in the mirror.

15:28.720 --> 15:30.305
That's deep.

15:30.388 --> 15:33.391
How do I feel...

15:33.475 --> 15:35.477
about myself?

15:36.603 --> 15:38.188
Uh...

15:42.692 --> 15:44.027
Yeah, I do.

15:44.110 --> 15:45.654
I feel pretty.

15:45.737 --> 15:47.364
Cool.

15:49.115 --> 15:51.284
You have dirt on your face.

15:55.538 --> 15:58.124
Please, girls,
we're going to be late.

15:58.208 --> 15:59.542
What is that?

16:00.585 --> 16:02.253
It's a dress.

16:02.337 --> 16:03.546
I made it.

16:03.630 --> 16:05.006
-Why?
-I don't know.

16:05.090 --> 16:06.257
I-I just thought,

16:06.341 --> 16:07.967
since the whole kingdom
will be there today,

16:08.051 --> 16:11.763
I could find someone
who will maybe buy it.

16:17.519 --> 16:19.396
To think that any girl,
let alone you,

16:19.479 --> 16:21.606
would have the audacity
to engage

16:21.690 --> 16:23.983
in matters of business,
it's insane.

16:24.067 --> 16:26.778
I will not have you
embarrassing this household

16:26.861 --> 16:28.655
with your blasphemy.

16:28.738 --> 16:30.824
Don't ever let me catch you
trying such nonsense again.

16:32.367 --> 16:34.411
Put the dress down.

16:35.453 --> 16:36.454
Yes, Stepmother.

16:41.126 --> 16:42.585
Good.

16:42.669 --> 16:45.213
Now... shoulders back.

16:45.296 --> 16:46.715
-No slouching.

16:47.757 --> 16:49.634
And smile.

16:49.718 --> 16:52.387
Every girl is worth more
when she smiles.

17:21.082 --> 17:23.251
What are you doing?

17:23.334 --> 17:27.672
I am stewing in my own anger.

17:27.756 --> 17:28.673
Oh, okay.

17:28.757 --> 17:30.508
You turned down the daughter

17:30.592 --> 17:31.926
of Lord Reginald.

17:32.010 --> 17:33.219
I guess she wasn't the one.

17:33.303 --> 17:34.637
She was!

17:34.721 --> 17:37.348
I would've had control
of all the territories

17:37.432 --> 17:39.517
right up to the domain
of the sea monster.

17:39.601 --> 17:41.728
Well, perhaps you should marry
the sea monster, Robert.

17:41.811 --> 17:43.396
I would have to have
grandmother's ring resized.

17:44.522 --> 17:46.357
You keep overlooking
his behavior,

17:46.441 --> 17:48.359
-and he'll never grow out of it.
-Stop.

17:48.443 --> 17:49.944
He's gonna make a fine king.

17:51.654 --> 17:53.281
Is it me,

17:53.364 --> 17:57.202
or is your throne
just a little bit taller

17:57.285 --> 17:58.620
-than it was yesterday?
-

17:58.703 --> 18:00.955
-I mean, it really looks...
-Oh, don't be ridiculous.

18:01.039 --> 18:02.165
-Quite a bit.
-And even if it is,

18:02.248 --> 18:04.459
I have every right
to make it taller.

18:04.542 --> 18:05.585
I'm king.

18:05.668 --> 18:08.046
Mm. Yes.

18:09.339 --> 18:10.757
And I am ridiculous.

18:10.840 --> 18:14.052
If you need me,
I shall be in my chambers.

18:14.135 --> 18:15.887
Brushing my hair.

18:15.970 --> 18:17.764
Until it all falls out.

18:17.847 --> 18:20.183
So we good?
'Cause I got a thing.

18:20.266 --> 18:22.352
Uh-uh-uh-uh-uh-uh-uh-uh.

18:22.435 --> 18:25.104
You're bringing shame
on this family, Robert.

18:25.188 --> 18:27.190
Have you seen this?

18:27.273 --> 18:29.734
ROBERT: "The Roundabout Players
present The King's Idiot Son."

18:29.818 --> 18:31.569
Ooh, do you think
we can still get tickets?

18:31.653 --> 18:33.029
I'm becoming a laughingstock.

18:33.112 --> 18:34.614
I think you're overreacting.

18:34.697 --> 18:36.282
Well, why don't you ask
the Roundabout Players

18:36.366 --> 18:37.534
if I'm overreacting?

18:37.617 --> 18:39.160
They are currently

18:39.244 --> 18:41.788
in a dark windowless room
under the castle.

18:43.248 --> 18:45.917
You can't leave actors alone
in a basement without attention.

18:46.000 --> 18:47.001
They'll die!

18:47.085 --> 18:48.545
When you marry,
you'll settle down.

18:48.628 --> 18:50.630
You'll stop behaving
like my idiot son,

18:50.713 --> 18:52.298
and the perception
of the people will be

18:52.382 --> 18:54.175
that you take the crown
seriously.

18:54.259 --> 18:55.468
-You can't control me.
-

18:55.552 --> 18:56.886
Oh, that's exactly
what I can do.

18:56.970 --> 18:58.346
That's the perk
of being the king.

18:58.429 --> 18:59.722
But I feel nothing
for these women.

18:59.806 --> 19:00.890
It's crazy to think
I'm actually gonna

19:00.974 --> 19:01.975
fall in love with one of them.

19:02.058 --> 19:03.226
Kings marry for power,

19:03.309 --> 19:04.602
-not for love.
-

19:04.686 --> 19:06.229
Oh, well, it's perfect then
that Mother came with

19:06.312 --> 19:08.231
three castles
and a hundred horses,

19:08.314 --> 19:09.399
or I suppose
I never would've been born!

19:09.482 --> 19:11.109
-Silence!
-

19:19.242 --> 19:22.745
Don't talk about
what you don't understand. Hmm?

19:22.829 --> 19:27.000
Continue to defy me,
and just out of spite,

19:27.083 --> 19:31.087
I'll give it all-- the crown,

19:31.170 --> 19:33.006
the palace,

19:33.089 --> 19:36.092
everything-- to your sister.

19:36.175 --> 19:38.136
CHOIR:

19:38.219 --> 19:40.013
Leave us, Gwen.

19:46.352 --> 19:47.312
Sorry.

19:47.395 --> 19:49.022
I would be embarrassed

19:49.105 --> 19:52.400
if I wasn't so bored
with my life.

19:52.483 --> 19:55.278
But since I'm here,
I would love to stay

19:55.361 --> 19:57.113
and help sort out
this whole crown issue.

19:57.196 --> 19:58.656
You've been excused, Gwen.

19:58.740 --> 20:00.909
Right.

20:00.992 --> 20:03.786
But would this be a good time
for me to mention

20:03.870 --> 20:06.205
how the kingdom could use
the power of the wind

20:06.289 --> 20:07.874
-instead of burning
filthy coal? -Go!

20:11.085 --> 20:14.255
Father, you know how badly
I want to be king.

20:15.882 --> 20:18.051
Now, to make sure your nuptials

20:18.134 --> 20:21.179
are done properly and on my
schedule, we shall hold a ball.

20:21.262 --> 20:22.680
-No.

20:24.307 --> 20:26.476
Yes. We'll invite
every woman of worth.

20:26.559 --> 20:29.312
You'll dance.
You'll be charming.

20:29.395 --> 20:30.772
You shall find a bride.

20:30.855 --> 20:32.023
-Hmm?
-No, no, no.

20:32.106 --> 20:34.442
D-Dancing at these things
is so... mannered.

20:34.525 --> 20:35.443
