Look, I'm not ashamed
to admit that my mother

1:01:44.368 --> 1:01:46.620
is a wonderful, strong woman.

1:01:48.247 --> 1:01:49.748
We get along very well.

1:01:49.832 --> 1:01:52.167
-But not that well.
-

1:01:52.251 --> 1:01:53.460
My father, on the other hand,

1:01:53.544 --> 1:01:55.129
well, he-he's not exactly
getting any younger.

1:01:55.212 --> 1:01:57.881
-Oh! -Oh!
-

1:01:57.965 --> 1:01:59.007
I'm so sorry.

1:02:04.430 --> 1:02:06.140
Oh, my God.

1:02:06.223 --> 1:02:08.100
That didn't happen.
Didn't happen.

1:02:08.183 --> 1:02:09.893
And even if it did happen,
I'm magic,

1:02:09.977 --> 1:02:11.603
-so nobody can see me.
-Hi.

1:02:12.688 --> 1:02:14.064
-You look, you look
so different. -Me different?

1:02:14.148 --> 1:02:16.150
You're the one
who looks different!

1:02:16.233 --> 1:02:17.818
All clean and...

1:02:17.901 --> 1:02:19.862
-That's a nice jacket.
-

1:02:19.945 --> 1:02:21.780
Why would you let me speak
so poorly of you to your face?

1:02:21.864 --> 1:02:24.366
-I admit it was deceitful,
but... -

1:02:24.450 --> 1:02:26.535
I mean, it worked. Here you are.

1:02:26.618 --> 1:02:28.412
Yes, and I am leaving.

1:02:28.495 --> 1:02:31.290
I've seen the dresses,
I drank the bubble drink,

1:02:31.373 --> 1:02:33.375
and now I actually have a chance
to make my dreams come true.

1:02:33.459 --> 1:02:35.002
So I'm gonna go.

1:02:35.085 --> 1:02:36.628
I'm gonna go
while I'm still ahead.

1:02:36.712 --> 1:02:37.838
Thank you.

1:02:37.921 --> 1:02:39.590
Well, you haven't seen
all of the dresses.

1:02:52.811 --> 1:02:55.772
Ladies and gentlemen,
I'd be remiss if I didn't take

1:02:55.856 --> 1:02:58.066
a moment to acknowledge
someone truly special.

1:03:00.027 --> 1:03:02.362
The people's princess,

1:03:02.446 --> 1:03:04.072
my little sister.

1:03:05.199 --> 1:03:06.200
Gwendolyn.

1:03:19.213 --> 1:03:20.756
CINDERELLA:
That's my dress.

1:03:20.839 --> 1:03:23.300
That's-that's my dress
on the princess.

1:03:23.383 --> 1:03:25.302
-Are you all right?
-

1:03:25.385 --> 1:03:27.596
I'm fine, I'm fine.
I just, uh...

1:03:27.679 --> 1:03:30.098
I need you to stop the room
from spinning.

1:03:30.182 --> 1:03:32.184
Perhaps this will work.

1:03:33.519 --> 1:03:35.896
M-Maybe would you like to dance?

1:03:35.979 --> 1:03:37.689
Right now?

1:04:22.192 --> 1:04:28.824
the someone waiting for me

1:04:54.641 --> 1:04:57.185
-

1:05:19.791 --> 1:05:22.878
our favorite song

1:05:58.372 --> 1:06:01.583
our favorite song

1:06:05.212 --> 1:06:11.843
an angel in person

1:06:15.555 --> 1:06:19.601
-

1:06:19.685 --> 1:06:23.522
-

1:06:27.150 --> 1:06:29.152
-

1:06:37.536 --> 1:06:40.539
Would you care to talk
alone somewhere?

1:06:40.622 --> 1:06:42.249
Lead the way.

1:06:48.255 --> 1:06:50.841
-What's it like being a crate?

1:06:50.924 --> 1:06:52.634
Like, this has got to be
a step up, right?

1:06:52.718 --> 1:06:54.845
-ROBERT: So this is
the fountain. -CINDERELLA: Ooh.

1:06:54.928 --> 1:06:56.638
ROBERT: Do you have
a fountain where you live?

1:06:56.722 --> 1:06:57.848
CINDERELLA:
Um, I don't.

1:06:57.931 --> 1:07:00.559
I just have
streaming water sometimes.

1:07:01.601 --> 1:07:03.228
-What is that? What is that?
-Did you hear that? That.

1:07:04.479 --> 1:07:07.190
-What?!
-This is bloody brilliant.

1:07:07.274 --> 1:07:08.900
What even is that?

1:07:10.068 --> 1:07:12.404
-We're just banging 'em
together. -I know.

1:07:12.487 --> 1:07:14.698
Humans can be so loud.

1:07:22.998 --> 1:07:24.541
-CINDERELLA: You make me
nervous. -ROBERT: Aw.

1:07:24.624 --> 1:07:28.295
Everything about tonight
is insane, right?

1:07:28.378 --> 1:07:30.922
B-Blink once
if you can understand me.

1:07:32.132 --> 1:07:33.300
-

1:07:33.383 --> 1:07:34.593
-ROBERT: You all right?
-CINDERELLA: Yeah.

1:07:34.676 --> 1:07:36.219
-Thanks for the jacket.
-ROBERT: Yeah.

1:07:36.303 --> 1:07:38.221
No, it's not like
I'm cold or anything.

1:07:41.183 --> 1:07:43.226
-Here we are.
-Wow.

1:07:44.644 --> 1:07:47.063
It's beautiful.

1:07:48.106 --> 1:07:49.649
Oh, um, I should probably
take my shoes off.

1:07:49.733 --> 1:07:50.734
-Right?
-Oh, no, you're fine.

1:07:50.817 --> 1:07:53.403
This floor is literally
2,000 years old.

1:07:54.988 --> 1:07:56.823
-So no?
-You're fine.

1:07:56.907 --> 1:07:59.201
-Okay.
-

1:08:03.455 --> 1:08:05.707
Are you gonna play something
on the piano just for me?

1:08:07.542 --> 1:08:09.377
Oh, my God, you are.

1:08:37.948 --> 1:08:39.950
Wow.

1:08:40.033 --> 1:08:43.161
You're so full
of hidden talents.

1:08:43.245 --> 1:08:45.372
So it sounds like you might
disagree with those who say

1:08:45.455 --> 1:08:48.041
I "serve no real purpose
other than to wreck things"?

1:08:49.084 --> 1:08:50.377
Just so you know,

1:08:50.460 --> 1:08:52.045
I don't actually think
those things about you.

1:08:52.128 --> 1:08:53.296
Especially now.

1:08:54.422 --> 1:08:55.632
Well, you should.

1:08:56.675 --> 1:08:57.843
Wh-Why?

1:08:57.926 --> 1:09:01.221
I mean, you're in line
to be our future king.

1:09:01.304 --> 1:09:03.098
Oh, it's a bad system.

1:09:03.181 --> 1:09:04.099
My only qualification being

1:09:04.182 --> 1:09:06.852
-that my dad was one.
-Mm.

1:09:08.812 --> 1:09:11.815
It's not that
I don't want to be king.

1:09:11.898 --> 1:09:15.193
When I was little,
I remember watching my father

1:09:15.277 --> 1:09:18.780
go off to war
and thinking how...

1:09:18.864 --> 1:09:21.074
brave he looked in his armor.

1:09:22.492 --> 1:09:25.328
And I wanted to be
just like him.

1:09:25.412 --> 1:09:30.250
And then, as I got older
and my life became

1:09:30.333 --> 1:09:33.169
more about
traditions and customs

1:09:33.253 --> 1:09:38.091
and people always watching me
and telling me what to do...

1:09:40.010 --> 1:09:45.390
...and never asking
what I want or how I feel...

1:09:46.433 --> 1:09:48.393
I know exactly what you mean.

1:09:53.273 --> 1:09:54.399
What?

1:09:54.482 --> 1:09:56.276
I just had...

1:09:56.359 --> 1:09:58.653
no idea
tonight would go like this.

1:09:59.696 --> 1:10:02.449
This is precisely
how I hoped tonight would go.

1:10:03.700 --> 1:10:05.535
You're the one.

1:10:07.370 --> 1:10:09.122
I pick you to be my princess.

1:10:10.457 --> 1:10:12.375
What's wrong?

1:10:12.459 --> 1:10:14.127
I-I assure you
it doesn't matter to me

1:10:14.210 --> 1:10:15.337
that you're not of royal birth.

1:10:15.420 --> 1:10:16.546
No, that's not it.

1:10:16.630 --> 1:10:18.131
W-We'll get married.

1:10:18.214 --> 1:10:19.591
Okay? We'll-we'll get married

1:10:19.674 --> 1:10:21.551
and you will live the rest
of your life as royalty.

1:10:21.635 --> 1:10:23.929
Royalty? What about my work?

1:10:24.012 --> 1:10:25.096
M-My dresses can...

1:10:25.180 --> 1:10:27.599
Well, that would
most likely be frowned upon.

1:10:27.682 --> 1:10:29.643
Women have
a very prescribed role in court.

1:10:29.726 --> 1:10:31.645
-"Prescribed role in court"?
-But I would make sure

1:10:31.728 --> 1:10:33.355
that you were dressed by
the finest dressmakers

1:10:33.438 --> 1:10:35.148
-in all the land.
-I'm a dressmaker.

1:10:35.231 --> 1:10:37.150
I know. There's just
no one else in this world

1:10:37.233 --> 1:10:38.443
I'd rather be with than you.

1:10:38.526 --> 1:10:39.861
Robert, stop.

1:10:41.279 --> 1:10:43.406
I don't want a life stuck
waving from a royal box

1:10:43.490 --> 1:10:45.867
any more than a life
confined to a basement.

1:10:45.951 --> 1:10:49.371
I have dreams
that I have to chase.

1:10:51.081 --> 1:10:53.333
So if it's a choice...

1:10:56.461 --> 1:10:58.088
...I choose me.

1:11:05.011 --> 1:11:06.513
I understand.

1:11:10.809 --> 1:11:14.020
Really, I... I do.

1:12:21.046 --> 1:12:23.048
I'm sorry.

1:12:35.185 --> 1:12:36.311
What time is it?

1:12:36.394 --> 1:12:37.937
It's midnight.

1:12:39.022 --> 1:12:40.148
I have to go.

1:12:40.231 --> 1:12:41.357
Wait!

1:12:42.400 --> 1:12:44.235
-I don't like this.

1:12:44.319 --> 1:12:46.696
-Some-Something's changed.
-Relax. We are fine.

1:12:46.780 --> 1:12:48.031
JOHN:
Ah!

1:12:48.114 --> 1:12:49.157
You just cleaned
phantom whiskers.

1:12:49.240 --> 1:12:51.076
-No, I did not.
-You did, too.

1:12:51.159 --> 1:12:54.120
-

1:12:54.204 --> 1:12:55.997
TATIANA:
Where are you off to, my dear?

1:12:56.081 --> 1:12:58.291
Am I to assume
I've lost you to the prince?

1:12:58.374 --> 1:13:00.919
No, my queen. I'll meet you
tomorrow, I promise.

1:13:01.753 --> 1:13:03.588
What's happening?

1:13:03.671 --> 1:13:05.799
My good people,
your future queen.

1:13:05.882 --> 1:13:08.384
-

1:13:17.310 --> 1:13:18.436
Help.

1:13:18.520 --> 1:13:20.021
This way. This way.

1:13:21.231 --> 1:13:22.649
Wilbur.

1:13:22.732 --> 1:13:23.900
Mm.

1:13:23.983 --> 1:13:26.194
You go.
I'll take care of this.

1:13:26.277 --> 1:13:28.363
Thank you so much.
I'll never forget this.

1:13:28.446 --> 1:13:30.115
Neither will I.

1:13:31.783 --> 1:13:33.785
The magic's wearing off.

1:13:33.868 --> 1:13:35.954
-What are we gonna do?
-What did the butterfly say?

1:13:36.037 --> 1:13:38.206
He called us disgusting,
that jerk.

1:13:38.289 --> 1:13:39.791
About the magic.
What was said about the magic?

1:13:39.874 --> 1:13:42.085
I don't know.
I was singing.

1:13:42.168 --> 1:13:44.254
-Why didn't you pay attention?
-Because I was singing!

1:13:44.337 --> 1:13:45.839
-
continues indistinctly)

1:13:50.260 --> 1:13:51.886
Dress your feet for comfort!

1:13:52.804 --> 1:13:54.347
-Get in.
-

1:13:54.430 --> 1:13:56.307
-Halt, I say!
-

1:14:00.895 --> 1:14:02.397
JAMES:
Come on, quick!

1:14:03.773 --> 1:14:05.733
-Get in! Quickly! Hurry!
-JOHN: Come on!

1:14:14.659 --> 1:14:17.036
Look. She threw
a glass shoe at me.

1:14:19.956 --> 1:14:22.250
I-I feel all tingly.

1:14:22.333 --> 1:14:23.918
Like I'm gonna...

1:14:25.920 --> 1:14:27.505
Now I'm feeling tingly.

1:14:27.589 --> 1:14:29.382
I don't want to go...

1:14:32.635 --> 1:14:35.263
Don't look at me!
Don't look at me!

1:14:37.849 --> 1:14:39.767
ROMESH: I'm starting
to feel a bit funny.

1:14:39.851 --> 1:14:41.269
I feel tingly!

1:14:41.352 --> 1:14:42.604
-CINDERELLA: No!

1:14:52.280 --> 1:14:53.948
No!

1:15:10.048 --> 1:15:11.132
Are we going down?

1:15:11.216 --> 1:15:12.258
-We're going down.
-

1:15:12.342 --> 1:15:13.635
Just be quiet as a mouse.

1:15:18.514 --> 1:15:19.933
Hmm.

1:15:20.016 --> 1:15:21.267
JAMES:
Maybe we're not going...

1:15:47.877 --> 1:15:50.338
Mm, mm, mm, mm.

1:15:50.421 --> 1:15:53.675
All the townspeople's
tax dollars

1:15:53.758 --> 1:15:56.094
wasted on a ball, and for what?

1:15:56.177 --> 1:15:59.055
For you to make
a complete fool out of me?

1:15:59.138 --> 1:16:00.807
To teach me a lesson?

1:16:00.890 --> 1:16:02.225
I'm sorry, Father.

1:16:02.308 --> 1:16:04.936
You are single-handedly
destroying my legacy.

1:16:05.019 --> 1:16:08.022
I know you might not
understand this,

1:16:08.106 --> 1:16:10.316
but the woman I chose
didn't choose me.

1:16:10.400 --> 1:16:12.277
Oh, I'm sorry, darling.

1:16:14.070 --> 1:16:15.780
Aw.

1:16:15.863 --> 1:16:17.448
Have you lost your mind?!

1:16:17.532 --> 1:16:19.826
You are the future king,

1:16:19.909 --> 1:16:24.080
and as king, it is all about you
and your power.

1:16:24.163 --> 1:16:26.124
There are no other opinions.
None.

1:16:31.170 --> 1:16:32.714
Is this a good time to ask

1:16:32.797 --> 1:16:34.507
why we are spending money
on catapults

1:16:34.590 --> 1:16:36.509
-when we have so many already?
-

1:16:36.592 --> 1:16:38.636
It really just benefits
the catapult makers.

1:16:38.720 --> 1:16:40.596
Quiet, Gwen!

1:16:40.680 --> 1:16:42.473
I really think we just need
to get some sleep.

1:16:42.557 --> 1:16:44.100
No one asked you, Beatrice.

1:16:53.609 --> 1:16:55.111
Your time is up, Robert.

1:16:56.904 --> 1:17:00.199
You will marry Princess Laura
by week's end.

1:17:00.283 --> 1:17:02.618
I don't care
if you don't love each other.

1:17:03.995 --> 1:17:05.788
So says the king.

1:17:12.253 --> 1:17:15.882
If the crown demands it...

1:17:15.965 --> 1:17:17.800
milord.

1:17:22.347 --> 1:17:24.015
Darling.

1:17:32.482 --> 1:17:33.900
What?

1:17:34.942 --> 1:17:36.527
Did you really just say
you don't care

1:17:36.611 --> 1:17:37.945
if they love each other?

1:17:38.988 --> 1:17:40.656
Yeah. I want the sea monster.

1:17:40.740 --> 1:17:42.575
What? Bea-Bea-Beatrice,
don't be...

1:17:42.658 --> 1:17:44.494
Ay... ay, ay, ay.

1:17:44.577 --> 1:17:45.912
-Your Highness.
-Yes?

1:17:45.995 --> 1:17:47.789
-Where'd you find that?
-It's the girl's.

1:17:47.872 --> 1:17:51.125
She threw it at my head.
I'm lucky to be alive.

1:18:02.887 --> 1:18:04.055
Look at our girl.

1:18:04.138 --> 1:18:05.848
Been up all night working.

1:18:05.932 --> 1:18:08.142
-She's betting on herself.
-JAMES: I couldn't do it.

1:18:08.226 --> 1:18:09.685
I would've married the prince.

1:18:09.769 --> 1:18:12.063
You think the prince
would've picked you?

1:18:12.146 --> 1:18:14.524
Cuddly, cute, good at waving.

1:18:14.607 --> 1:18:15.775
I mean, come on.

1:18:17.860 --> 1:18:19.404
I can hear you.

1:18:19.487 --> 1:18:20.988
I bet you're arguing about why

1:18:21.072 --> 1:18:23.741
I didn't just say yes
to marrying Robert.

1:18:23.825 --> 1:18:26.786
Especially since I'm maybe
in love with him.

1:18:26.869 --> 1:18:28.496
JOHN:
Love? It was one night.

1:18:28.579 --> 1:18:29.872
-

1:18:29.956 --> 1:18:32.208
I never felt what I felt
last night before.

1:18:33.835 --> 1:18:36.295
I mean, you guys,
he's so handsome.

1:18:36.379 --> 1:18:37.797
-Oh, yes, he is incredibly
handsome. -Absolutely.

1:18:37.880 --> 1:18:39.507
-Annoyingly handsome.
-The cheekbones.

1:18:39.590 --> 1:18:40.758
And he likes me for me.

1:18:40.842 --> 1:18:42.301
Sounds like true love
to this mouse.

1:18:42.385 --> 1:18:44.095
You're right, my friend.

1:18:44.178 --> 1:18:47.098
But if saying yes to him

1:18:47.181 --> 1:18:50.017
means saying no to this...

1:18:51.102 --> 1:18:53.729
...I can't do it.

1:18:53.813 --> 1:18:55.648
All right, guys?

1:18:55.731 --> 1:18:59.444
I have to try and make a life
for myself, by myself.

1:18:59.527 --> 1:19:01.946
Because that is what I want.

1:19:02.029 --> 1:19:04.198
And Queen Tatiana is my chance.

1:19:04.282 --> 1:19:05.533
Right.

1:19:05.616 --> 1:19:06.993
-Who's Queen Tatiana?
-

1:19:07.076 --> 1:19:08.286
VIVIAN:
Cinderella, are you down there?

1:19:08.369 --> 1:19:09.579
-Stepmother?
-Dear God, no.

1:19:09.662 --> 1:19:11.497
-She scares me.
-Me, too.

1:19:11.581 --> 1:19:15.084
-Hello.
I'm waiting for my tea.

1:19:15.168 --> 1:19:17.587
Cinderella.
Oh, I'm coming down.

1:19:25.428 --> 1:19:26.721
I'm sick.

1:19:27.847 --> 1:19:29.599
Uh-huh.

1:19:36.731 --> 1:19:38.900
Well, you didn't miss much
at the ball.

1:19:41.736 --> 1:19:44.989
The prince was fixated
on some mystery girl.

1:19:46.574 --> 1:19:49.285
Then she ran away like a twit.

1:19:49.368 --> 1:19:52.747
So now he's to marry
Princess Laura of Northphalia

1:19:52.830 --> 1:19:54.373
the day after next.

1:19:54.457 --> 1:19:57.543
Malvolia and Narissa,
they never stood a chance.

1:19:58.586 --> 1:20:01.130
And I was so foolish
to believe differently.

1:20:02.423 --> 1:20:04.967
A mother just gets carried away.

1:20:07.345 --> 1:20:09.555
I know I've been hard on you.

1:20:10.932 --> 1:20:12.767
It's not fueled by spite.

1:20:24.153 --> 1:20:27.073
I've never shared this
with anyone before, but...

1:20:30.076 --> 1:20:32.119
I used to play piano.

1:20:32.203 --> 1:20:34.247
Taught myself.

1:20:36.082 --> 1:20:38.626
And I was good.

1:20:38.709 --> 1:20:41.754
I was really good.

1:20:43.881 --> 1:20:45.716
Nothing made me happier.

1:20:47.552 --> 1:20:50.596
Then one day,
I was given the opportunity

1:20:50.680 --> 1:20:53.724
to train at the finest
school of music,

1:20:53.808 --> 1:20:56.352
and I took it.

1:20:56.435 --> 1:20:58.354
There I was--

1:20:58.437 --> 1:21:01.315
two children, a loving husband,

1:21:01.399 --> 1:21:04.944
and I had the audacity
to want more.

1:21:07.488 --> 1:21:11.033
It was just a month-- one month.

1:21:11.117 --> 1:21:15.371
And yet, when I returned,
my husband, well...

1:21:17.248 --> 1:21:20.209
...he believed real wives
didn't act so frivolously.

1:21:27.341 --> 1:21:29.510
You may think me cruel.

1:21:37.893 --> 1:21:40.479
But the real cruelty would be
for me to allow you to think

1:21:40.563 --> 1:21:42.315
that you can be
something you can't.

1:21:57.872 --> 1:21:59.290
This shoe.

1:22:04.795 --> 1:22:06.339
It was you.

1:22:06.422 --> 1:22:07.882
Cinderella.

1:22:07.965 --> 1:22:10.593
I don't know how you did
what you did last night,

1:22:10.676 --> 1:22:12.720
but the prince chose you.
He loves you.

1:22:12.803 --> 1:22:14.930
Marry him, and all of
our problems will be solved.

1:22:15.014 --> 1:22:17.433
