You haven't spoken to me
since last night.

1:26:23.012 --> 1:26:24.597
You're mad
because I yelled at you.

1:26:26.432 --> 1:26:29.143
I hate to break it to you,
but kings yell.

1:26:30.853 --> 1:26:33.355
Please, say something.

1:26:33.439 --> 1:26:35.649
You're making me
wildly uncomfortable.

1:26:38.611 --> 1:26:40.487
Have you ever wondered
why Robert makes

1:26:40.571 --> 1:26:42.448
the process to marry
so difficult?

1:26:42.531 --> 1:26:46.118
Because he's a spoiled child
who refuses to grow up. Simple.

1:26:46.201 --> 1:26:49.747
I believe it's because of the
example set before him by us.

1:26:49.830 --> 1:26:52.207
A marriage without love,
without respect.

1:26:52.291 --> 1:26:53.959
Bea, please,
you know I love you.

1:26:54.043 --> 1:26:55.711
Saying "love" and showing love

1:26:55.794 --> 1:26:58.380
are two very different things,
Rowan.

1:26:58.464 --> 1:27:01.842
Before you were king,
I felt your love every day.

1:27:01.926 --> 1:27:04.470
You couldn't stand to be away
from me, even for a moment.

1:27:04.553 --> 1:27:06.972
Remember, you used to appear
at my window

1:27:07.056 --> 1:27:08.974
like a knight in shining armor

1:27:09.058 --> 1:27:12.478
